# MOOD — Player Stats Dashboard

A full-stack player statistics dashboard for the video game Mood.
Built to demonstrate full-stack development with a REST API,
React frontend, data visualization, and Docker containerization.

## Tech Stack

| Layer       | Technology                        |
|-------------|-----------------------------------|
| Frontend    | React 18, Vite, Recharts          |
| Backend     | Node.js, Express.js               |
| Data        | JSON (swappable for PostgreSQL)   |
| DevOps      | Docker, docker-compose            |

## Running the App

### Prerequisites
- Docker Desktop installed and running

### Start

```bash
docker-compose up --build
```

Then open http://localhost:3000

## API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint            | Description                        |
|--------|---------------------|------------------------------------|
| GET    | /health             | Service health check               |
| GET    | /api/players        | Returns all players                |
| GET    | /api/players/:id    | Returns a single player by ID      |
| GET    | /api/leaderboard    | Returns players sorted by K/D      |

## Features

- Leaderboard sorted by K/D ratio with color coding
- Player profiles with kills, deaths, join date, last active
- Bar chart visualization of kills vs deaths per player
- Fully containerized — runs anywhere Docker is installed

